@endnode

@node CLOSEPATH

@{U}@{FG Highlight}CLOSEPATH                                                                   @{FG Text}@{UU}

Purpose: Closes the selected open polygon paths.

Syntax:  @{b}closepath@{ub} [PAGE number/S | WINDOW name/S | OBJECTID number/I]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         PAGE       is the page name. (Default=current)
         WINDOW     is the window name. (Default=current)
         OBJECTID   is the number of the object to manipulate.

Example: closepath page 'project.doc~6'

@{" Command Format    " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
@{" Object ID numbers " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/IDNU}
@{" DOCUMENT, CHAPTER, WINDOW, PAGE, MASTERPAGE, MPG, STYLETAG & ARTICLE " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/WIND}
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node CLOSEWINDOW

@{U}@{FG Highlight}CLOSEWINDOW                                                                 @{FG Text}@{UU}

Purpose: Close an open window.

Syntax:  @{b}closewindow@{ub} [WINDOW name/S]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         WINDOW     is the window name. (Default=current)

Note:    This command closes a single view of the document. To close all
         open views of a document, use the @{"CLOSEDOCUMENT" link closewindow} command.

Example: closewindow force window 'Untitled Document.1~View.1'

@{" Command Format    " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
@{" DOCUMENT, CHAPTER, WINDOW, PAGE, MASTERPAGE, MPG, STYLETAG & ARTICLE " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/WIND}
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node COLORPALETTE

@{U}@{FG Highlight}COLORPALETTE                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Purpose: Displays the color palette.

Syntax:  @{b}colorpalette@{ub} [SHOW | HIDE | TOGGLE] [AT pointx/I pointy/I]
         [SIZE width/I height/I] [SAVE]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         SHOW       toggles on the palette.
         HIDE       toggles off the palette.
         TOGGLE     toggles the palette on and off.
         AT         sets the palette position.
         SIZE       sets the palette size in pixels. (Min=160x50)
         SAVE       saves the values to PageStream3.prefs.

Note:    The TOGGLE parameter may not be used in conjunction with the SAVE
         parameter.

Example: colorpalette toggle
         colorpalette show at 500 300 size 180 172 save
         colorpalette hide

@{" Command Format    " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node CONVERTTOPATH

@{U}@{FG Highlight}CONVERTTOPATH                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Purpose: Converts an object to a path.

Syntax:  @{b}converttopath@{ub} [DOCUMENT name/S | WINDOW name/S | OBJECTID number/I]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         DOCUMENT   is the document name. (Default=current)
         WINDOW     is the window name. (Default=current)
         OBJECTID   is the number of the object to manipulate.

Example: converttopath
         converttopath window 'Untitled Document.1~View.1'

** currently broken

