@endnode

@node DUPLICATE

@{U}@{FG Highlight}DUPLICATE                                                                   @{FG Text}@{UU}

Purpose: Duplicates the selected object(s) once with a small offset.

Syntax:  @{b}duplicate@{ub} [OFFSET offsetx/D offsety/D]
         [DOCUMENT name/S | WINDOW name/S | OBJECTID number/I]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}  @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         OFFSET     overrides the default duplicate offsets.
         DOCUMENT   is the document name. (Default=current)
         WINDOW     is the window name. (Default=current)
         OBJECTID   is the number of the object to manipulate.

Example: duplicate offset 1.125 -2.5
         duplicate document 'project.doc'

See also @{"SETDUPLICATEDEFAULTS" link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MD5/setduplicatedefaults}.

@{" Command Format    " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
@{" Object ID numbers " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/IDNU}
